    <description><![CDATA[
# go-starter

Comprehensive Go project generator that combines the simplicity of create-react-app with the flexibility of Spring Initializr. Generate production-ready Go projects with modern best practices, multiple architecture patterns, and deployment configurations.

## Features

- **12 Project Types**: CLI, Web API, Lambda, Microservice, Library, and more
- **Multiple Architectures**: Standard, Clean Architecture, DDD, Hexagonal, Event-driven
- **Progressive Disclosure**: Smart interface that adapts to user experience level
- **Simplified Logger System**: Support for slog, zap, logrus, zerolog with 60-90% code reduction
- **Production Hardening**: Advanced AST operations, automated test generation, continuous monitoring
- **Cross-platform**: Windows, macOS, Linux support

## Quick Start

```
# Interactive mode (beginner-friendly)
go-starter new

# Direct generation
go-starter new my-app --type=cli --complexity=simple

# Advanced mode with all options  
go-starter new --advanced
```

## Supported Project Types

- **Simple CLI**: Quick utilities (8 files)
- **Standard CLI**: Production CLIs (29 files)  
- **Web API**: REST APIs with multiple architectures
- **Lambda**: AWS serverless functions
- **Microservice**: Distributed systems with gRPC
- **Library**: Reusable Go packages
- **Workspace**: Multi-module monorepos

## Architecture Patterns

- **Standard**: Traditional layered architecture
- **Clean Architecture**: Enterprise-grade separation of concerns
- **DDD**: Domain-driven design with rich models
- **Hexagonal**: Ports & adapters for maximum testability
- **Event-driven**: CQRS and event sourcing patterns

This tool dramatically accelerates Go development by providing battle-tested project structures and eliminating the need to repeatedly configure common patterns.
